what is role role binding cluster cluster binding?

    >>Role
✅ Defines permissions within a single namespace
A Role specifies what actions are allowed (get, create, delete, etc.) on which resources (pods, services, deployments) inside one namespace.
📌 Namespace‑scoped
RoleBinding
✅ Grants a Role to a user/group/service account in a namespace
A RoleBinding connects a Role to users or groups, giving them the permissions defined in the Role within that namespace.
📌 Namespace‑scoped

Defines permissions across the entire cluster
A ClusterRole specifies permissions that apply cluster‑wide or to non‑namespaced resources like nodes, namespaces, PVs.
ClusterRoleBinding
✅ Grants a ClusterRole to a user/group/service account across the cluster

A ClusterRoleBinding gives cluster‑wide access based on the ClusterRole.
📌 Cluster‑scoped
